        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-10 10:42:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI was thinking it would be good to add a sanity test for this (after checking server version >= 2.13.53 to avoid a crash), using \"lfs setstripe -C 2000\" or similar to overstripe the file, which would be good for testing anyway.\n\nHowever, I found that sanity.sh test_27Cd is already testing with \"-C 2000\".  Is there something about your 511-stripe case that would be different so that the failure isn't triggered by that test?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b3b147bbe7ab6e72a710e57be375f8f6eefdae4c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 793,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "adegremont@nvidia.com",
        "username": "degremoa"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-10 20:40:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nInteresting, I did not think about using overstripping. I will try to dig into that.  But overstriping is not an old feature.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
