      },
      "date": "2020-05-04 13:01:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> However, I found that sanity.sh test_27Cd is already testing with \"-C 2000\".  Is there something about your 511-stripe case that would be different so that the failure isn't triggered by that test?\n\nI finally find time to test that with Lustre 2.12.4 and I could reproduce the same crash.\n\nI don't know if overstriping is handled differently and this assert is not reachable anymore, but I'm sure that until overstriping is landed, the bug is there.",
